# DESIGN SYSTEM

Apply under `web/`. Consult `core.mdc`, `frontend.mdc` first.

## Skills (read first)

`shadcn`, `tailwind-patterns`, `frontend-design`, `web-design-guidelines`, `ui-ux-pro-max`

## Principles

- **Density with clarity** — trading terminal layout; numbers legible at a glance
- **Latency felt** — skeletons within ~100ms; optimistic UI only when API contract allows
- **Buy vs Sell** — never color-only; pair hue with label/icon
- **WCAG 2.1 AA floor** — labels, focus rings, contrast on tables and forms

## Stack

- Tailwind v4 `@theme` tokens in `styles/globals.css`
- shadcn primitives in `components/ui/` — add via CLI, customize in repo
- Icons: **lucide-react** only
- Charts: **lightweight-charts** for OHLCV

## Layout (MVP)

| Zone | Content |
|------|---------|
| Primary | Order entry + candlestick chart |
| Secondary | Order book, trade tape, open orders |
| Account | Wallet, holdings, P&L |

Prices: 4 decimals · Quantities: integers · Currency: USD

## Tokens

Use semantic classes — **no raw hex in JSX**:

`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-destructive`

Buy/sell accents via dedicated utilities or CSS variables (e.g. `--color-bid`, `--color-ask`) defined in `@theme`, not inline `#…`.

## Components

- Tables: compact rows, sticky header, monospace optional for prices/qty
- Order status: pill with text + color
- Loading: shadcn `Skeleton` / Query `isPending` — avoid layout shift on book updates
- Errors: inline `FormMessage` + border — not color-only

## Accessibility checklist

- [ ] Every input has `<Label>` / `htmlFor`
- [ ] Icon-only buttons have `aria-label`
- [ ] Focus visible (`focus-visible:ring-2`)
- [ ] Status changes use `aria-live="polite"` where appropriate
- [ ] Keyboard-operable order form

## DON'TS

- ❌ No second component library
- ❌ No bespoke modal/dialog — shadcn primitives
- ❌ No generic “AI dashboard” aesthetic — restrained financial terminal
- ❌ No emojis as primary affordances
